{"lemma":"تُرْجُمانِ","slug":"تُرْجُمانِ","root":"ت.ر.ج.م","root_slug":"ت-ر-ج-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ر-ج-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14984","n3861"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"translator"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interpreter, dragoman","examples":[{"text":"مَا مِنْكُم مِن أَحَدٍ إِلَّا سَيُكَلَّمُهُ رَبُّهُ لَيْسَ بَيْنَهُ وَبَيْنَهُ تُرْجُمَانٌ","english":"Everyone of you will speak to his Lord without an interpreter between them."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cicerone"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"guide"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Classical Syriac ܬܰܪܓܡܳܢܳܐ (targmānā, “interpreter”), itself from Akkadian 𒅴𒁄 (targumannum, “interpreter”); see the root entry for further information.\nCognate of Hebrew תֻּרְגְּמָן (turgmán)."},"ipa":["/tur.d͡ʒu.maːn/","/tar.d͡ʒu.maːn/","/tar.d͡ʒa.maːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14984","headword_ar":"تَرْجُمَانٌ","root":"rjm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turojumaAnN","text_ar":"تُرْجُمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarojamaAnN","text_ar":"تَرْجَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraAjimu","text_ar":"تَرَاجِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraAjimapN","text_ar":"تَرَاجِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trjm","text_ar":"ترجم"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3861","headword_ar":"تَرْجُمَانٌ","root":"trjm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turojumaAnN","text_ar":"تُرْجُمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarojamaAnN","text_ar":"تَرْجَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjm","text_ar":"رجم"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Msb and K in the present art.,) of which three dial. vars. the first is the best, (Msb,) and is that which commonly obtains, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An interpreter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an explainer of speech in another language:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a translator:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see the verb, above:)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraAjimu","text_ar":"تَرَاجِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraAjimapN","text_ar":"تَرَاجِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which latter favours the opinion of those who hold the word to be of foreign origin. (S, Msb.) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"are [said to be] radicals; but J makes the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be augmentative, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trjmAn","text_ar":"ترجمان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned in the T [as well as in the S] in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjm","text_ar":"رجم"},{"kind":"text","text":", though the author of the T has mentioned the verb among quadriliteral-radical words; and there is a reason [for deriving it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajama","text_ar":"رَجَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], for one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnN yarojumu","text_ar":"لِسَانٌ يَرْجُمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ a tongue that is chaste, or perspicuous, and copious, in speech: ” most, however, hold the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be a radical. (Msb.) It is said in the K that the verb shows the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be radical; whereas J and AHei and IKt hold it to be augmentative; but there is a difference of opinion whether it be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajomu","text_ar":"الرَّجْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlHijaArapi","text_ar":"بِالحِجَارَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the throwing stones], or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajomu","text_ar":"الرَّجْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlgayobi","text_ar":"بِالغَيْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the conjecturing, or speaking conjecturally]; and also whether it be Arabic, or arabicized from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"drgmAn","text_ar":"درغمان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a word which I do not know in Persian nor in any other language]: (MF, TA:) if arabicized, the present is its proper place. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","S","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}